# -----------------------------------------------------
# DATABASE (Supabase PostgreSQL) - REQUIRED
# -----------------------------------------------------
# Get Supabase connection string:
# 1. Go to https://supabase.com/dashboard
# 2. Select your project (or create one - free tier available)
# 3. Go to Project Settings → Database
# 4. Scroll to "Connection string" section
# 5. Select "URI" tab
# 6. Copy the connection string
# 7. Replace [YOUR-PASSWORD] with your database password from when you created the project
#
# Format: postgresql://postgres:[YOUR-PASSWORD]@db.xxxxx.supabase.co:5432/postgres
# Example: postgresql://postgres:mySecretP@ssw0rd@db.tktrwwwjudjumg.vyh.supabase.co:5432/postgres
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres.tklrwxmujpdjujmglyvh:TKcF2xL8Fj6OVgwZ@aws-1-us-east-1.pooler.supabase.com:5432/postgres



